# Overview
Dockerizing CloudForms 4.1 (CFME) for building CloudForms demos.
Based on registry.access.redhat.com/cloudforms/cfme4:latest, adds database dump
from the environment in the MBU lab.

# Prerequisites
- git
- GitHub account
- Docker Engine
- RedHat VPN access

# Usage
Build docker container.
$ sh bin/init.sh

Run docker container.
$ docker run --privileged -di -p 80:80 -p 443:443 --name cfme4-demo ecwpz91/cfme4-demo

SSH into the docker container.
$ docker exec -it cfme4-demo /bin/bash

Stop the docker container.
$ docker stop cfme4-demo

Remove the docker container.
$ docker rm cfme4-demo 

# Credentials
Open a browser to "https://localhost/" and login with 'admin' & 'smartvm' (default password).

